title: New Jersey’s Rising Coastal Risk
description: Changes in the climate since the 1980s have put a growing share of New Jersey’s coastal communities at risk. This report quantifies the impact of sea-level rise and changes in hurricane activity over the past four decades and explores the economic implications for the state in the years ahead.
